==Esperanto==
===Etymology===
Esperanto ''[[ti-]]'' (demonstrative [[:Category:Esperanto correlatives|correlative]] prefix) + ''[[-om]]'' (correlative suffix of quantity)

===Correlative===
'''tiom'''

# [[that]] [[much]] (demonstrative correlative of quantity)
#: As with other demonstrative correlatives in Esperanto, ''[[tiom]]'' can be combined with ''[[ĉi]]'', the adverbial particle of proximity, or with ''[[for]]'', the adverbial particle of distance. ''Tiom ĉi'' thus means ''this much [as I am indicating]'' and ''tiom for'' means ''that much [as indicated by someone else]''.

